<div id="review_478730821" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/478730821" />
    <a title="Michael" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13532739-michael"><img alt="Michael" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1600647973p2/13532739.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/478730821?book_show_action=true">Dec 16, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael" href="/user/show/13532739-michael">Michael</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781101601099" href="/book/show/16692561-the-tale-of-the-heike">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer478730821" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9817214600393848352">Royall Tyler&apos;s translation conveys the tremendous range of this medieval classic, one of the central narratives in the Japanese tradition, and one of the world&apos;s great narratives of war. Three earlier translations were all in prose, but Tyler uses prose and two forms of verse, following closely the three ways in which the war tale was originally recited, chanted, and sung. The fall of the Heike family is a story that echoes throughout later Japanese culture--many noh plays are based on events fr</span>
  <span id="freeText9817214600393848352" style="display:none">Royall Tyler's translation conveys the tremendous range of this medieval classic, one of the central narratives in the Japanese tradition, and one of the world's great narratives of war. Three earlier translations were all in prose, but Tyler uses prose and two forms of verse, following closely the three ways in which the war tale was originally recited, chanted, and sung. The fall of the Heike family is a story that echoes throughout later Japanese culture--many noh plays are based on events from the tale. It deserves to be much better known by readers outside of Japan. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9817214600393848352" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

