<span id="freeTextContainer10862956692662994893">This was just incredible. This medieval tale covers one of the key events in Japanese history when the Genji defeated the Heike and set up the Kamakura shogunate removing the Emperor from the centre of power. There is much court intrigue, many omens and acts of bravery on both sides. <br/>This reminded me of The Odyssey in many ways, but it was so Japanese at the same time. <br/>All Japanophiles should read this! Tyler&apos;s translations are great. Sorry I took so l long to read it.</span>
  <span id="freeText10862956692662994893" style="display:none">This was just incredible. This medieval tale covers one of the key events in Japanese history when the Genji defeated the Heike and set up the Kamakura shogunate removing the Emperor from the centre of power. There is much court intrigue, many omens and acts of bravery on both sides. <br />This reminded me of The Odyssey in many ways, but it was so Japanese at the same time. <br />All Japanophiles should read this! Tyler's translations are great. Sorry I took so l long to read it.</span>
